Hi there, 

This new feature returns some details (path, parent path, and value) of a corresponding key. I implemented this method because I needed it in a specific situation and I did not find it in any library. I use lodash and I think it fits perfectly into this package in the Object category.

[findKeyDeep.txt](https://github.com/lodash/lodash/files/2161483/findKeyDeep.txt)

example:
```
const users = {
  'biruel': {
    'age': 38,
    'location': {
      'liveIn': {
        'country': 'brazil',
        'flag': 'br.jpg',
      },
      'WorkOn': {
        'country': 'spain',
        'flag': 'es.jpg',
      },
    },
  },
};

findKeyDeep(users, 'flag').then(x => console.log(x));
// out => [
  {
    item: 1,
    path: 'biruel.location.liveIn.flag',
    value: 'br.jpg',
    parentPath: 'biruel.location.liveIn'
  },
  {
    item: 2,
    path: 'biruel.location.WorkOn.flag',
    value: 'es.jpg',
    parentPath: 'biruel.location.WorkOn'
  }
];

findKeyDeep(users, 'since').then(x => console.log(x));
// out => false;
```
Thanks to all
