In the documentation for `_.create()`, the prototype argument appears to be required, but this is not the case.  If the prototype argument is not an object, lodash simply returns `{}`.

This is an important distinction from `Object.create()`, which throws an error if the prototype argument is not an object (this means `null` is permitted as `typeof null === 'object'`, but `undefined` is not permitted).

```
> _.create();
{}
> Object.create();
TypeError: Object prototype may only be an Object or null: undefined
```

